export const TERMS_HTML = "<p>These Terms and Conditions (\"<strong>Terms</strong>\") govern your access to and use of the Broadbase platform (the \"<strong>Platform</strong>\"), operated by Eventide Limited (\"<strong>Broadbase</strong>\", \"<strong>we</strong>\", \"<strong>us</strong>\", or \"<strong>our</strong>\").</p><p>By creating an Account or using the Platform in any capacity, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms in full.</p><p><strong>If you do not agree to these Terms, you must not create an Account or use the Platform.</strong></p><h2 id=\"1-definitions\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">1.</span> Definitions</h2><p>In these Terms, the following expressions have the meanings set out below:</p><p><strong>\"Account\"</strong> means a registered user account created to access the Platform.</p><p><strong>\"AI Features\"</strong> means the AI-powered writing assistant, AI research assistant, and AI Readiness Score functionality described in Section 10.</p><p><strong>\"Asset\"</strong> means any file attached to a Press Release, including images, PDFs, videos, and documents.</p><p><strong>\"Brand\"</strong> means a company, organisation, or public relations agency that accesses the Platform on the supply side to upload and manage Press Releases and Assets.</p><p><strong>\"Brand User\"</strong> means an individual who accesses the Platform on behalf of a Brand under a paid Subscription.</p><p><strong>\"Content\"</strong> means Press Releases, Assets, and any other material uploaded to the Platform by Users.</p><p><strong>\"Digest\"</strong> means the personalised email summary of Press Releases sent to Journalists on a scheduled basis as described in Section 12.</p><p><strong>\"Embargo Date\"</strong> means a future date and time specified by a Brand before which a Press Release must not be published, broadcast, or otherwise disclosed by any party.</p><p><strong>\"Journalist\"</strong> means an individual who accesses the Platform on the demand side to discover, search, save, and download Press Releases and Assets for legitimate editorial purposes.</p><p><strong>\"Journalist Portfolio\"</strong> means the public, search-engine-indexed profile page associated with a Journalist Account, displaying that Journalist's editorial beats and published bylines as voluntarily submitted.</p><p><strong>\"Platform\"</strong> means the Broadbase web application, application programming interfaces (APIs), and associated services accessible at broadbase.io and its subdomains.</p><p><strong>\"Press Release\"</strong> means a written editorial announcement uploaded to the Platform by a Brand User.</p><p><strong>\"Subscription\"</strong> means a paid plan (Solo, Growth, or Enterprise) that grants a Brand User access to supply-side features of the Platform.</p><p><strong>\"User\"</strong> means any individual who creates an Account on the Platform, whether as a Brand User or Journalist.</p><h2 id=\"2-eligibility-and-account-registration\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">2.</span> Eligibility and Account Registration</h2><p><strong>2.1</strong> You must be at least 18 years of age and have the legal capacity to enter into a binding contract under the laws of your jurisdiction in order to use the Platform.</p><p><strong>2.2</strong> If you are registering on behalf of a company or organisation, you represent and warrant that you have the authority to bind that entity to these Terms, and that the entity accepts these Terms.</p><p><strong>2.3</strong> You must provide accurate, complete, and current information during registration and maintain the accuracy of that information throughout the life of your Account. Providing false or misleading information is a material breach of these Terms.</p><p><strong>2.4</strong> You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your Account login credentials. You must not share your credentials with any third party. You are responsible for all activity that occurs under your Account, whether authorised by you or not.</p><p><strong>2.5</strong> You must notify Broadbase immediately upon becoming aware of any unauthorised access to, or use of, your Account.</p><p><strong>2.6</strong> Accounts are personal and non-transferable. You may not sell, assign, or otherwise transfer your Account to any other person or entity.</p><p><strong>2.7</strong> Broadbase reserves the right to decline registration, suspend, or terminate any Account at its sole discretion, including where it has reason to believe that the information provided is inaccurate, that the Account is being misused, or that you have breached these Terms.</p><h2 id=\"3-user-types-and-roles\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">3.</span> User Types and Roles</h2><p><strong>3.1 Brand Users.</strong> Brand Users access the Platform to upload Press Releases and Assets, manage one or more Brand profiles, and view engagement analytics associated with their Content. Brand Users must maintain a paid Subscription as set out in Section 4.</p><p><strong>3.2 Journalists.</strong> Journalists access the Platform free of charge to discover, search, save, and download Press Releases and Assets for legitimate editorial purposes. Journalist access is conditional on the Journalist providing accurate information about their publication and editorial beats at registration. Broadbase reserves the right to verify Journalist credentials and to suspend or remove Journalist Accounts where credentials cannot be verified or are found to be inaccurate.</p><p><strong>3.3</strong> User type is fixed at registration and is not convertible. You may not use a single Account for both Brand User and Journalist purposes. If you require access in both capacities, you must register a separate Account for each role.</p><h2 id=\"4-subscription-plans-and-payment\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">4.</span> Subscription Plans and Payment</h2><h3 id=\"4-1-plans\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">4.1 Plans</h3><p>Brand Users must subscribe to one of the following plans to access supply-side features of the Platform. All fees are denominated in Hong Kong Dollars (HKD) and are exclusive of any applicable taxes, duties, or levies.</p><table><thead><tr><th><p><strong>Plan</strong></p></th><th><p><strong>Monthly Fee</strong></p></th><th><p><strong>Brand Profiles Permitted</strong></p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><p>Solo</p></td><td><p>HK$780 per month</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Growth</p></td><td><p>HK$2,340 per month</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Enterprise</p></td><td><p>HK$6,240 per month</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id=\"4-2-free-trial\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">4.2 Free Trial</h3><p>New Brand Users are entitled to a 14-day free trial upon registration, during which supply-side features are accessible without payment. At the end of the trial period, a paid Subscription is required to continue accessing supply-side features. Broadbase reserves the right to modify or discontinue the free trial offer at any time.</p><h3 id=\"4-3-billing\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">4.3 Billing</h3><p>Subscriptions are billed on a recurring monthly basis. Payment is collected via Stripe. By providing your payment details and initiating a Subscription, you authorise Broadbase to charge the applicable fee automatically on each monthly billing date. You are responsible for ensuring that valid payment details are maintained on your Account.</p><h3 id=\"4-4-price-changes\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">4.4 Price Changes</h3><p>Broadbase reserves the right to revise Subscription fees. Where fees are to be increased, Broadbase will provide not less than 30 days' prior written notice via the email address associated with your Account. Continued use of the Platform after the effective date of a price change constitutes your acceptance of the revised fees.</p><h3 id=\"4-5-cancellation-and-refunds\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">4.5 Cancellation and Refunds</h3><p>You may cancel your Subscription at any time via your Account settings. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the then-current monthly billing period, after which access to supply-side features will cease. No refunds or credits are issued for any unused portion of a billing period. Downgrading your plan takes effect at the start of the next billing period.</p><h3 id=\"4-6-suspension-for-non-payment\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">4.6 Suspension for Non-Payment</h3><p>If a payment fails or is declined, Broadbase may suspend or restrict access to supply-side features until payment is successfully received. Broadbase will make reasonable attempts to notify you of a payment failure before suspending your Account.</p><h3 id=\"4-7-brand-profile-limits\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">4.7 Brand Profile Limits</h3><p>The number of Brand profiles you may create is limited to the number specified for your plan as set out in Section 4.1. The Platform will reject any attempt to create Brand profiles in excess of your plan limit. You may increase your limit by upgrading to a higher plan. Downgrading to a lower plan does not automatically delete existing Brand profiles that exceed the new limit; however, no new profiles may be created until the number of active profiles is within the lower plan's limit.</p><p>Each Brand profile permitted under your selected Subscription tier corresponds strictly to <strong>one (1) unique legal corporate entity or single registered brand trademark</strong>. </p><p>Public relations agencies, consultancies, or multi-brand conglomerates utilising the Platform on behalf of multiple underlying clients are strictly prohibited from renaming, swapping, modifying, or rotating a single Brand Profile slot to manage multiple distinct clients or projects over time. Each distinct client or brand asset collection requires its own designated, permanent Brand Profile slot within the Platform's infrastructure. </p><p>Broadbase reserves the right to run automated and manual compliance audits on profile update histories. Any profile rotation detected to intentionally circumvent subscription tier thresholds will result in immediate retroactive billing to the appropriate Subscription tier or account suspension. </p><h3 id=\"4-8-taxes\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">4.8 Taxes</h3><p>You are solely responsible for all taxes, goods and services taxes, value added taxes, withholding taxes, duties, and similar governmental charges applicable to your use of the Platform, unless Broadbase is expressly required by law to collect and remit them on your behalf.</p><h2 id=\"5-content-brand-user-obligations\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">5.</span> Content — Brand User Obligations</h2><h3 id=\"5-1-ownership-and-licence\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">5.1 Ownership and Licence</h3><p>You retain ownership of all Content you upload to the Platform. By uploading Content, you grant Broadbase a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free, sublicensable licence to store, process, display, and distribute that Content solely to the extent necessary to operate and provide the Platform, including making Content discoverable by Journalists and transmitting Content in Digest emails.</p><p>This licence terminates when Content is permanently deleted from the Platform, subject to any retention obligations under applicable law or these Terms.</p><ol><li><strong>Retention of Ownership:</strong> You retain all right, title, and interest, including all intellectual property rights, in and to all Content and Assets you upload to the Platform. Broadbase claims no ownership over your Content. You acknowledge and agree that Broadbase acts strictly as a passive technological intermediary, host, and database provider (similar to cloud storage or file transfer utilities) for the distribution of your materials.</li><li><strong>License Grant:</strong> By uploading Content, you grant Broadbase a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free, fully sublicensable, and transferable license to host, store, cache, process, modify (solely for technical formatting, indexing, and display optimization), translate, distribute, and surface that Content to Demand-Side users (Journalists). This license includes the right to make such Content available to automated web crawlers and large language models (LLMs) as detailed in Section 10.</li></ol><h3 id=\"5-2-accuracy-and-truthfulness\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">5.2 Accuracy and Truthfulness</h3><p>You represent and warrant that all Content you upload is accurate, truthful, complete, and not misleading. Press Releases must reflect genuine announcements. You must not upload Content that contains fabricated facts, invented quotations, false statistics, or unsubstantiated claims.</p><h3 id=\"5-3-rights-clearance\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">5.3 Rights Clearance</h3><p>You represent and warrant that:</p><ul><li>(a) you hold all rights, licences, consents, and permissions necessary to upload Content to the Platform and to grant the licence described in Section 5.1;</li><li>(b) your Content does not infringe the intellectual property, privacy, or other rights of any third party; and</li><li>(c) any individuals quoted or depicted in your Content have given their informed consent to be quoted or depicted in that context.</li></ul><h3 id=\"5-4-embargo-conditions\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">5.4 Embargo Conditions</h3><p>If you apply an Embargo Date to a Press Release:</p><ul><li>(a) Broadbase will withhold that Press Release from discovery by Journalists until the Embargo Date has passed;</li><li>(b) Broadbase does not independently communicate embargo conditions to Journalists beyond the information surfaced on the Platform; and</li><li>(c) You remain solely responsible for communicating any additional embargo terms or conditions to parties outside the Platform, and for enforcing embargo compliance with third parties.</li></ul><p>Broadbase does not guarantee that all Journalists who access embargoed material will comply with embargo obligations. Broadbase's obligations with respect to embargo enforcement are limited to the technical controls described in (a) above.</p><h3 id=\"5-5-prohibited-content\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">5.5 Prohibited Content</h3><p>You must not upload Content that:</p><ul><li>(a) is defamatory, fraudulent, deliberately misleading, or deceptive;</li><li>(b) infringes any third-party intellectual property rights, including copyright, trade marks, or database rights;</li><li>(c) violates any individual's privacy, data protection, or publicity rights;</li><li>(d) constitutes spam or unsolicited mass commercial solicitation;</li><li>(e) contains malicious code, viruses, trojan horses, or any content designed to disrupt or damage systems;</li><li>(f) promotes illegal activity;</li><li>(g) is obscene, hateful, or discriminatory; or</li><li>(h) is otherwise objectionable, as determined by Broadbase in its sole discretion.</li></ul><h3 id=\"5-6-moderation\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">5.6 Moderation</h3><p>Broadbase reserves the right to review, withhold from discovery, moderate, or permanently remove any Content at any time and without prior notice, where it determines that Content violates these Terms or is otherwise unsuitable for the Platform. Moderation decisions are made at Broadbase's sole discretion. No refunds are issued in connection with the moderation or removal of Content.</p><h3 id=\"5-7-no-guarantee-of-discovery-or-coverage\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">5.7 No Guarantee of Discovery or Coverage</h3><p>Broadbase provides an infrastructure for content publishing and journalist-led discovery. We make no representation, warranty, or guarantee that:</p><ul><li>(a) any Press Release will be discovered, read, downloaded, or acted upon by Journalists;</li><li>(b) any Press Release will result in editorial coverage of any kind; or</li><li>(c) the number of Journalists registered on the Platform will remain constant.</li></ul><p>The Platform's value to Brand Users lies in access to a pull-based discovery infrastructure and real-time engagement analytics — not in guaranteed editorial outcomes.</p><h2 id=\"6-content-journalist-obligations\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">6.</span> Content — Journalist Obligations</h2><h3 id=\"6-1-permitted-use\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">6.1 Permitted Use</h3><p>As a Journalist, you may access, download, and use Content from the Platform solely for legitimate editorial and journalistic purposes, including the preparation and publication of editorial articles, reviews, and reports. You must not:</p><ul><li>(a) commercially resell, redistribute, sublicence, or otherwise exploit Content for purposes unrelated to genuine editorial coverage;</li><li>(b) reproduce substantial portions of a Press Release verbatim in published editorial work without appropriate attribution; or</li><li>(c) use downloaded Assets for commercial advertising, promotional, or marketing purposes.</li><li><strong>(d) </strong>Access to the Platform is granted strictly to facilitate legitimate, immediate editorial coverage. Under no circumstances shall a Journalist or Brand use, copy, extract, scrape, or compile data, content, or contact information from the Platform to: i. Build, update, or maintain an independent, competing media database, media list, or public relations directory. ii. Conduct commercial market research, competitive intelligence, or data analytics for non-editorial third parties or commercial entities. iii. Extract, harvest, or export contact information or platform metadata to build separate distribution lists for unsolicited communications. Any violation of this Section 6.1(d) constitutes an immediate, material breach of these Terms, resulting in instantaneous account termination and potential legal liability for trade secret misappropriation.</li></ul><h3 id=\"6-2-embargo-obligations\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">6.2 Embargo Obligations</h3><p>By accessing a Press Release that displays an Embargo Date, you unconditionally and irrevocably agree to:</p><ul><li>(a) refrain from publishing, broadcasting, transmitting, or otherwise disclosing any information derived from that Press Release, in any medium, until the Embargo Date has passed;</li><li>(b) treat all embargoed material as strictly confidential until the Embargo Date; and</li><li>(c) take all reasonable steps to ensure that no individual at your publication, employer, or organisation publishes or discloses embargoed material in advance of the Embargo Date.</li></ul><h3 id=\"6-3-consequences-of-embargo-breach\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">6.3 Consequences of Embargo Breach</h3><p>A breach of Section 6.2 constitutes a material breach of these Terms and may result in immediate suspension or permanent termination of your Journalist Account without notice. Broadbase reserves the right to notify the relevant Brand of any confirmed or suspected embargo breach. You acknowledge that an embargo breach may cause the Brand material harm, and you may be liable to the Brand directly under applicable law.</p><h3 id=\"6-4-accuracy-of-journalist-profile\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">6.4 Accuracy of Journalist Profile</h3><p>You represent and warrant that:</p><ul><li>(a) the publication name, editorial role, beats, and any other profile information you provide are accurate and current;</li><li>(b) you are a working journalist, editor, or legitimate editorial professional; and</li><li>(c) you will update your profile information promptly if it becomes inaccurate.</li></ul><p>Misrepresentation of journalistic credentials or editorial affiliation is a material breach of these Terms and grounds for immediate Account termination.</p><h3 id=\"6-5-journalist-portfolio\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">6.5 Journalist Portfolio</h3><p>The Journalist Portfolio feature allows you to maintain a public, search-engine-indexed record of your editorial bylines and published work. By submitting content to your Journalist Portfolio, you:</p><ul><li>(a) confirm that all published articles you list accurately reflect your editorial output;</li><li>(b) grant Broadbase a non-exclusive licence to display that information publicly on the Platform and in search engine indexes; and</li><li>(c) acknowledge that your Journalist Portfolio is publicly accessible and may be viewed by Brand Users and other parties.</li></ul><p>You may update or remove entries from your Journalist Portfolio at any time via your Account settings.</p><h3 id=\"6-6-no-commercial-relationship\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">6.6 No Commercial Relationship</h3><p>Access to the Platform as a Journalist is provided free of charge. Nothing in these Terms creates an employment, agency, retainer, or contractor relationship between you and Broadbase or between you and any Brand. Broadbase does not compensate Journalists for any activity on the Platform.</p><p><strong>6.7 Account Currency and Professional Affiliation</strong> Journalists must maintain an active, monitored corporate or professional email address associated with their current media publication or freelance practice. If a Journalist’s corporate email address becomes inactive, bounces, or fails delivery verification, Broadbase reserves the right to immediately suspend platform access without notice pending identity and affiliation re-verification.</p><h2 id=\"7-platform-use-general\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">7.</span> Platform Use — General</h2><h3 id=\"7-1-prohibited-conduct\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">7.1 Prohibited Conduct</h3><p>Regardless of user type, you must not:</p><ul><li>(a) use the Platform for any purpose that is unlawful under the laws of Hong Kong or any other applicable jurisdiction;</li><li>(b) attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the Platform, its underlying systems, or any third-party systems integrated with the Platform;</li><li>(c) reverse-engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise attempt to derive source code from any part of the Platform;</li><li>(d) use automated tools, bots, crawlers, scrapers, or scripts to access, index, extract, or copy data from the Platform without Broadbase's prior written authorisation;</li><li>(e) introduce or transmit malicious code, viruses, or any material designed to damage, interfere with, or disrupt the Platform;</li><li>(f) impersonate any person or entity or misrepresent your affiliation with any person or entity;</li><li>(g) attempt to circumvent or defeat any security control, rate limit, access control, or embargo enforcement mechanism implemented by the Platform;</li><li>(h) use the Platform to send unsolicited commercial communications of any kind; or</li><li>(i) engage in any conduct that Broadbase determines, in its sole discretion, to be harmful to the Platform, its Users, or the reputation of Broadbase.</li></ul><h3 id=\"7-2-acceptable-use\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">7.2 Acceptable Use</h3><p>Your use of the Platform must at all times comply with these Terms and all applicable laws. Broadbase reserves the right to investigate any suspected breach of these Terms and to take such action as it deems appropriate, including temporary or permanent suspension of your Account, removal of Content, or referral to law enforcement authorities.</p><h2 id=\"8-intellectual-property\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">8.</span> Intellectual Property</h2><h3 id=\"8-1-platform-ip\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">8.1 Platform IP</h3><p>All intellectual property rights in the Platform, including its software, architecture, design, interface, trademarks, brand name, logos, and documentation, are owned by or licensed to Broadbase. Nothing in these Terms grants you any right, title, or interest in the Platform's intellectual property other than the limited licence to use it strictly in accordance with these Terms.</p><h3 id=\"8-2-broadbase-trade-marks\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">8.2 Broadbase Trade Marks</h3><p>\"Broadbase\" and any associated logos and brand identifiers are trade marks of Broadbase. You must not use these marks without Broadbase's prior written consent. You must not register any domain name, trade mark, or company name that is identical to or confusingly similar to \"Broadbase\".</p><h3 id=\"8-3-feedback\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">8.3 Feedback</h3><p>If you submit feedback, suggestions, ideas, or improvement requests to Broadbase regarding the Platform, you grant Broadbase a perpetual, irrevocable, royalty-free, worldwide licence to use, incorporate, and commercialise that feedback without restriction, attribution, or compensation to you.</p><h2 id=\"9-analytics-and-data\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">9.</span> Analytics and Data</h2><h3 id=\"9-1-engagement-analytics-for-brand-users\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">9.1 Engagement Analytics for Brand Users</h3><p>Broadbase provides Brand Users with engagement data relating to their Press Releases and Assets, including view counts, asset download counts, and AI Readiness Scores. This data is intended to help Brand Users understand how their Content is performing on the Platform.</p><h3 id=\"9-2-journalist-anonymity\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">9.2 Journalist Anonymity</h3><p>Engagement analytics provided to Brand Users are aggregated and anonymised. Broadbase will not disclose the identity, contact details, publication name, or other personally identifiable information of individual Journalists to Brand Users. Any attempt by Brand Users to identify specific individuals from aggregated analytics data is prohibited and constitutes a breach of these Terms.</p><h3 id=\"9-3-no-ave-reporting\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">9.3 No AVE Reporting</h3><p>Broadbase does not calculate or report Advertising Value Equivalent (AVE) as a metric. AVE is a discredited methodology for measuring public relations value. Broadbase's analytics are based on direct engagement data — views, downloads, and AI Readiness Scores — which are meaningfully different from AVE calculations.</p><h3 id=\"9-4-accuracy-of-analytics\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">9.4 Accuracy of Analytics</h3><p>Analytics data is provided on a reasonable efforts basis. Broadbase does not warrant the accuracy, completeness, or timeliness of analytics data. You must not make material financial or strategic decisions based solely on Platform analytics data without independent verification. Broadbase shall not be liable for decisions made in reliance on analytics data.</p><h2 id=\"10-ai-features\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">10.</span> AI Features</h2><h3 id=\"10-1-ai-writing-assistant-brand-users\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">10.1 AI Writing Assistant (Brand Users)</h3><p>The Platform includes an AI-powered writing assistant to help Brand Users improve the readability and structure of draft Press Releases. When using this feature:</p><ul><li>(a) all AI-generated suggestions are presented as a side-by-side comparison with your original draft and require your explicit acceptance before being saved;</li><li>(b) the AI is designed to improve clarity, structure, and editorial flow only — it must not be used to introduce facts, quotes, statistics, or claims not present in your original draft;</li><li>(c) you are solely responsible for reviewing, verifying, and approving all AI-generated content before publishing it to the Platform; and</li><li>(d) published Content containing AI-assisted copy remains subject to all accuracy and rights obligations in Section 5.</li></ul><h3 id=\"10-2-ai-research-assistant-journalists\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">10.2 AI Research Assistant (Journalists)</h3><p>The Platform includes an AI research assistant to help Journalists identify story angles and connections within Press Releases available on the Platform. When using this feature:</p><ul><li>(a) the assistant draws only on Press Releases retrieved from the Platform — it does not access external knowledge sources, the internet, or information outside the Platform's content;</li><li>(b) the assistant may return limited or no results if no matching Press Releases are available for a given query;</li><li>(c) assistant responses do not constitute verified facts and must be independently verified before use in published editorial work; and</li><li>(d) the assistant is not a substitute for independent journalistic research, source verification, or editorial judgement.</li></ul><h3 id=\"10-3-ai-readiness-score\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">10.3 AI Readiness Score</h3><p>The Platform calculates an AI Readiness Score for each published Press Release based on structural and content criteria, including title length, body word count, the presence of quotes, images, and PDFs, tag count, and summary length. The score is expressed as a number from 0 to 100 and is intended as a practical optimisation tool for Brand Users.</p><p>The AI Readiness Score is indicative only. Broadbase makes no representation or warranty that a higher score will result in greater Journalist discovery, engagement, or editorial coverage. The score reflects structural criteria only and does not assess the editorial quality, newsworthiness, or factual accuracy of Content.</p><h3 id=\"10-4-rate-limits\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">10.4 Rate Limits</h3><p>AI Feature usage may be subject to rate limits. Broadbase reserves the right to modify rate limits at any time. Attempts to circumvent rate limits are prohibited under Section 7.1.</p><h3 id=\"10-5-no-warranty-on-ai-output\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">10.5 No Warranty on AI Output</h3><p>Broadbase does not warrant the accuracy, completeness, fitness for purpose, or originality of any AI-generated content or suggestions. AI Features are provided as-is. You use them entirely at your own risk. Broadbase shall not be liable for any harm, loss, or liability arising from your reliance on or use of AI-generated output.</p><h3 id=\"10-6-generative-engine-optimisation-geo-and-database-crawling\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">10.6 Generative Engine Optimisation (GEO) and Database Crawling</h3><p><strong>(a) Purpose of AI Readiness:</strong> The AI Readiness Score and structural optimization tools provided by the Platform are designed to achieve two objectives: (i) to format Content for optimal readability by Journalists, and (ii) to enhance Generative Engine Optimisation (GEO). This structuring assists Large Language Models (LLMs), AI search agents, and automated retrieval systems in accurately categorizing, parsing, and reflecting the Brand User’s information within public and private AI systems. </p><p><strong>(b) LLM and Crawler Authorization:</strong> By publishing Content on the open or discoverable sections of the Platform, Brand Users explicitly acknowledge and agree that Broadbase may permit third-party LLMs, conversational AI engines, and search indexers to crawl, index, and ingest the published Content and Assets. This is executed in the interest of Maximizing the digital reach, search visibility, and factual accuracy of the Brand User's clients within AI-generated search results. </p><p><strong>(c) Limitation of Liability for AI Outputs:</strong> Broadbase does not operate or control third-party LLMs or search engines. We make no warranty or guarantee regarding how external AI platforms will interpret, display, misinterpret, or alter the Content uploaded by users. Broadbase shall not be held liable for any inaccuracies, hallucinations, or omissions generated by third-party AI platforms utilizing data indexed from Broadbase. </p><h2 id=\"11-file-uploads-and-security\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">11.</span> File Uploads and Security</h2><p><strong>11.1</strong> All file uploads to the Platform are subject to server-side validation for file type, size, and content. Broadbase reserves the right to reject uploads that fail validation checks without prior notice.</p><p><strong>11.2</strong> The maximum permitted file size for any single upload is 50 megabytes (MB). Broadbase may change this limit at any time.</p><p><strong>11.3</strong> Accepted file types are limited to: JPEG, PNG, WebP, and GIF images; PDF documents; MP4 and MOV video files; and Microsoft Word documents. Broadbase reserves the right to modify the list of accepted file types.</p><p><strong>11.4</strong> You must not attempt to upload files that are disguised or misrepresented as a permitted file type. The Platform performs server-side MIME-type detection and will reject files whose true type does not match an accepted type.</p><p><strong>11.5</strong> Hero images uploaded to the Platform are stored in a publicly accessible storage location and may be embedded in Digest emails, public release pages, and Open Graph previews without authentication. All other Assets are stored in a restricted access location and are accessible to Journalists only via time-limited, signed download URLs generated by the Platform.</p><h2 id=\"12-email-communications-and-digest\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">12.</span> Email Communications and Digest</h2><p><strong>12.1</strong> By creating a Journalist Account, you consent to receiving the Broadbase Digest — a periodic email summary of newly published Press Releases curated to your editorial beats. The Digest is sent on a daily or weekly basis depending on your preferences, which you may configure in your Account settings.</p><p><strong>12.2</strong> You may unsubscribe from the Digest at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link included in each Digest email. Unsubscribing does not delete your Account.</p><p><strong>12.3</strong> Both Brand Users and Journalists consent to receiving transactional and operational emails from Broadbase relating to their Account, including account verification, billing notifications, password resets, and material updates to these Terms. These emails are necessary for the operation of your Account and cannot be opted out of while your Account remains active.</p><h2 id=\"13-privacy-and-data-protection\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">13.</span> Privacy and Data Protection</h2><p><strong>13.1</strong> Your use of the Platform is subject to Broadbase's Privacy Policy, which is incorporated into these Terms by reference. The Privacy Policy sets out how Broadbase collects, processes, stores, and shares personal data in connection with the Platform.</p><p><strong>13.2</strong> By creating an Account and using the Platform, you acknowledge that you have read the Privacy Policy and consent to the processing of your personal data as described therein.</p><p><strong>13.3</strong> Where you upload Content that includes personal data of third parties (for example, a quoted individual's name), you are solely responsible for ensuring that your collection and use of that personal data complies with all applicable data protection laws, including the Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance (Cap. 486) of Hong Kong and any other applicable legislation.</p><p><strong>13.4 </strong>To the extent that the Content, Press Releases, or Assets uploaded by a User involve the cross-border transfer, collection, or processing of personal data across the Asia-Pacific region, the uploading User represents, warrants, and guarantees full compliance with all applicable regional data privacy frameworks. This includes, but is not limited to, the Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance (Cap. 486) of Hong Kong, the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA) of Singapore, and any relevant regional privacy legislation. The User warrants that all necessary explicit consents from data subjects (including quoted individuals, executives, and brand representatives) have been legally obtained before transmitting such information through Broadbase’s cross-border hosting infrastructure. </p><h2 id=\"14-third-party-services\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">14.</span> Third-Party Services</h2><p><strong>14.1</strong> The Platform integrates with third-party service providers, including but not limited to Stripe (payment processing), Supabase (database and storage), Resend (email delivery), Vercel (hosting), and Google (AI services). Use of these services is subject to their respective terms of service and privacy policies.</p><p><strong>14.2</strong> Broadbase is not responsible for the availability, reliability, or conduct of third-party service providers. Any disruption to the Platform caused by a third-party service provider does not constitute a breach of these Terms by Broadbase.</p><p><strong>14.3</strong> Payment processing is carried out by Stripe. Broadbase does not store your full payment card details. By making a payment, you agree to Stripe's terms of service and privacy policy.</p><h2 id=\"15-platform-availability-and-modifications\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">15.</span> Platform Availability and Modifications</h2><p><strong>15.1</strong> Broadbase will use reasonable endeavours to maintain the availability of the Platform but does not guarantee uninterrupted or error-free access. The Platform may be unavailable during scheduled maintenance windows or due to circumstances outside Broadbase's reasonable control.</p><p><strong>15.2</strong> Broadbase reserves the right to modify, update, suspend, or discontinue any feature, aspect, or the entirety of the Platform at any time. Where a modification materially reduces the core functionality of a paid Subscription, Broadbase will endeavour to provide reasonable advance notice.</p><p><strong>15.3</strong> Broadbase may revise these Terms at any time by posting updated Terms on the Platform with a revised \"Last updated\" date. Where changes are material, Broadbase will provide notice to Users via the email address associated with their Account. Continued use of the Platform after the effective date of revised Terms constitutes your acceptance of those revised Terms. If you do not accept revised Terms, you must stop using the Platform and, if applicable, cancel your Subscription.</p><h2 id=\"16-disclaimer-of-warranties\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">16.</span> Disclaimer of Warranties</h2><p><strong>16.1</strong> TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, THE PLATFORM IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\" AND \"AS AVAILABLE\", WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, WHETHER EXPRESS, IMPLIED, STATUTORY, OR OTHERWISE.</p><p><strong>16.2</strong> BROADBASE EXPRESSLY DISCLAIMS ALL IMPLIED WARRANTIES, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.</p><p><strong>16.3</strong> BROADBASE DOES NOT WARRANT THAT:</p><ul><li>(a) THE PLATFORM WILL MEET YOUR REQUIREMENTS OR EXPECTATIONS;</li><li>(b) THE PLATFORM WILL OPERATE WITHOUT INTERRUPTION, DELAY, OR ERROR;</li><li>(c) ANY CONTENT ON THE PLATFORM IS ACCURATE, COMPLETE, CURRENT, OR RELIABLE;</li><li>(d) ANY DEFECTS OR ERRORS IN THE PLATFORM WILL BE CORRECTED; OR</li><li>(e) THE PLATFORM IS FREE FROM VIRUSES OR OTHER HARMFUL COMPONENTS.</li></ul><h2 id=\"17-limitation-of-liability\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">17.</span> Limitation of Liability</h2><p><strong>17.1</strong> TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, BROADBASE SHALL NOT BE LIABLE TO YOU FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES OF ANY KIND, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO:</p><ul><li>(a) LOSS OF PROFITS OR ANTICIPATED PROFITS;</li><li>(b) LOSS OF REVENUE OR BUSINESS;</li><li>(c) LOSS OF DATA OR CORRUPTION OF DATA;</li><li>(d) LOSS OF GOODWILL OR REPUTATION;</li><li>(e) LOSS OF EDITORIAL COVERAGE OR MEDIA OPPORTUNITIES; OR</li><li>(f) ANY OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSS,</li></ul><p>WHETHER ARISING IN CONTRACT, TORT (INCLUDING NEGLIGENCE), STATUTE, OR OTHERWISE, AND WHETHER OR NOT BROADBASE WAS ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.</p><p><strong>17.2</strong> TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, BROADBASE'S TOTAL AGGREGATE LIABILITY TO YOU FOR ALL CLAIMS ARISING UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THESE TERMS OR YOUR USE OF THE PLATFORM SHALL NOT EXCEED THE GREATER OF:</p><ul><li>(a) THE TOTAL SUBSCRIPTION FEES ACTUALLY PAID BY YOU TO BROADBASE IN THE THREE (3) CALENDAR MONTHS IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING THE EVENT GIVING RISE TO THE CLAIM; OR</li><li>(b) HK$1,000.</li></ul><p><strong>17.3</strong> NOTHING IN THESE TERMS SHALL EXCLUDE OR LIMIT BROADBASE'S LIABILITY FOR:</p><ul><li>(a) FRAUD OR FRAUDULENT MISREPRESENTATION;</li><li>(b) WILFUL MISCONDUCT OR GROSS NEGLIGENCE;</li><li>(c) DEATH OR PERSONAL INJURY CAUSED BY NEGLIGENCE; OR</li><li>(d) ANY OTHER LIABILITY THAT CANNOT BE LAWFULLY EXCLUDED OR LIMITED UNDER APPLICABLE LAW.</li></ul><h2 id=\"18-indemnification\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">18.</span> Indemnification</h2><p>You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Broadbase and its directors, officers, employees, contractors, and agents from and against any and all claims, proceedings, damages, liabilities, costs, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of or in connection with:</p><ul><li>(a) your use of the Platform in breach of these Terms;</li><li>(b) any Content you upload to the Platform, including any claim that your Content infringes the rights of a third party;</li><li>(c) your breach of any representation, warranty, or obligation set out in these Terms;</li><li>(d) your breach of an embargo obligation under Section 6.2; or</li><li>(e) your violation of any applicable law or regulation.</li></ul><h2 id=\"19-termination\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">19.</span> Termination</h2><h3 id=\"19-1-termination-by-you\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">19.1 Termination by You</h3><p>You may terminate your Account at any time by using the Account deletion feature within the Platform or by contacting Broadbase at the address set out in Section 21. For Brand Users, cancellation of a Subscription is governed by Section 4.5, and Account termination will not accelerate the end date of a billing period already paid for.</p><h3 id=\"19-2-termination-by-broadbase\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">19.2 Termination by Broadbase</h3><p>Broadbase may suspend or permanently terminate your Account immediately and without prior notice or liability if:</p><ul><li>(a) you commit a material breach of any provision of these Terms, including a breach of an embargo obligation;</li><li>(b) you misrepresent your identity, credentials, or affiliation;</li><li>(c) Broadbase is required to do so by applicable law or a competent regulatory authority;</li><li>(d) Broadbase reasonably determines that your use of the Platform poses a security risk, reputational risk, or harm to other Users; or</li><li>(e) you fail to pay Subscription fees and do not remedy the failure within 7 days of notice.</li></ul><h3 id=\"19-3-effect-of-termination\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">19.3 Effect of Termination</h3><p>Upon termination of your Account:</p><ul><li>(a) your right to access and use the Platform ceases immediately;</li><li>(b) Broadbase may delete your Account data in accordance with its data retention policies and Privacy Policy, subject to any legal obligations to retain data;</li><li>(c) for Brand Users, any Content published prior to termination that has already been downloaded by Journalists may remain in those Journalists' possession for legitimate editorial use;</li><li>(d) outstanding Subscription fees remain payable; and</li><li>(e) Broadbase is not obligated to provide copies of your data following termination, though it may do so at its discretion.</li></ul><h3 id=\"19-4-survival\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">19.4 Survival</h3><p>The following provisions survive termination of your Account and these Terms: Sections 8 (Intellectual Property), 9 (Analytics and Data), 15.3 (Revisions to Terms), 16 (Disclaimer of Warranties), 17 (Limitation of Liability), 18 (Indemnification), 19.3 (Effect of Termination), 19.4 (Survival), 20 (Governing Law and Disputes), and 21 (General).</p><h3 id=\"19-5-treatment-of-inactive-journalist-accounts\" class=\"legal-subsection-heading\">19.5 Treatment of Inactive Journalist Accounts</h3><p><strong>(a) Deactivation Criteria:</strong> Broadbase may designate a Journalist Account as \"Inactive\" if: (i) emails sent to the registered address consistently bounce or return hard delivery failures; or (ii) the account records zero login activity for a consecutive period of twelve (12) months.</p><p><strong>(b) Data Retention and Purging:</strong> Upon designation as Inactive, Broadbase will revoke access to the account. Personal data associated with the account will be handled as follows:</p><ul><li><strong>Journalist Portfolio &amp; Public Data:</strong> Any public-facing Journalist Portfolio or indexed profile page maintained on the Platform may be unindexed and permanently deleted from our servers to ensure database accuracy. </li><li><strong>Private Platform Data:</strong> Saved press releases, internal search history, and platform preferences will be permanently purged after a ninety (90) day grace period from the date of deactivation.</li><li><strong>Anonymized Analytics Retention:</strong> Operational data, including past download volume, view counts, and platform interactions, will be permanently stripped of all personal identifiers and retained in an aggregated, anonymized format to maintain the integrity of historical engagement analytics provided to Brand Users. <strong>(c) Re-activation:</strong> A journalist may reclaim their historical platform footprint prior to the ninety (90) day purge by contacting support and providing verified proof of their new professional editorial affiliation.</li></ul><h2 id=\"20-governing-law-and-disputes\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">20.</span> Governing Law and Disputes</h2><p><strong>20.1</strong> These Terms and any dispute, controversy, or claim arising out of or in connection with them — including disputes about their formation, validity, breach, termination, or non-contractual matters — shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China (\"<strong>Hong Kong SAR</strong>\").</p><p><strong>20.2</strong> The parties irrevocably submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of the Hong Kong SAR to resolve any dispute or claim arising under or in connection with these Terms or your use of the Platform.</p><p><strong>20.3</strong> Before commencing any formal legal proceedings, the parties agree to attempt in good faith to resolve any dispute through direct negotiation for a period of 30 days from the date on which one party notifies the other of the nature of the dispute. This clause does not prevent either party from seeking urgent injunctive or interim relief from a court of competent jurisdiction where necessary.</p><h2 id=\"21-general\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">21.</span> General</h2><p><strong>21.1 Entire Agreement.</strong> These Terms, together with the Privacy Policy and any other policies incorporated herein by reference, constitute the entire agreement between you and Broadbase with respect to the Platform. They supersede all prior and contemporaneous agreements, representations, warranties, and understandings, whether written or oral, relating to the same subject matter.</p><p><strong>21.2 Severability.</strong> If any provision of these Terms is found by a court of competent jurisdiction to be invalid, unlawful, or unenforceable, that provision shall be modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it valid, lawful, and enforceable, and the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect without alteration.</p><p><strong>21.3 Waiver.</strong> No failure or delay by Broadbase in exercising any right, power, or remedy under these Terms shall operate as a waiver of that right, power, or remedy. A single or partial exercise of any right, power, or remedy shall not preclude any other or further exercise of it.</p><p><strong>21.4 Assignment.</strong> You may not assign, transfer, delegate, or subcontract any of your rights or obligations under these Terms to any third party without Broadbase's prior written consent. Broadbase may assign its rights and obligations under these Terms without restriction, including in connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets.</p><p><strong>21.5 Notices.</strong> Notices from Broadbase to you will be sent to the email address associated with your Account or posted on the Platform. Notices from you to Broadbase regarding these Terms should be sent to: <a href=\"mailto:legal@broadbase.app\">legal@broadbase.app</a></p><p><strong>21.6 No Third-Party Beneficiaries.</strong> These Terms are for the sole benefit of the parties hereto and do not confer any rights or remedies upon any third party.</p><p><strong>21.7 Force Majeure.</strong> Broadbase shall not be liable for any delay or failure to perform any obligation under these Terms where such delay or failure arises from circumstances beyond Broadbase's reasonable control, including acts of God, natural disasters, epidemic or pandemic, war, terrorism, civil unrest, governmental action or regulation, internet outages, or failures of third-party infrastructure or service providers. Broadbase will notify you as soon as reasonably practicable of any such event and will use reasonable endeavours to resume performance.</p><p><strong>21.8 Relationship of Parties.</strong> Nothing in these Terms creates a partnership, joint venture, agency, franchise, employment, or fiduciary relationship between you and Broadbase.</p><p><strong>21.9 Language.</strong> These Terms are written in the English language. In the event of any inconsistency between an English version and any translation, the English version shall prevail.</p><h2 id=\"22-contact\" class=\"legal-section-heading\"><span class=\"legal-section-number\">22.</span> Contact</h2><p>For questions, concerns, or notices regarding these Terms, please contact Broadbase at:</p><p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"mailto:legal@broadbase.app\">legal@broadbase.app</a><br /><strong>Website:</strong> <a href=\"https://broadbase.app\">broadbase.app</a></p><p><em>© 2026 Broadbase. All rights reserved.</em></p>";
